<HL>
   Amstar to Sell Milford Unit
</HL>
<DATE>
12/28/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE 16
</SO>
<CO>
   X.ASR S.SAN
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
DIVERSIFIED INDUSTRIAL (IDD)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW HAVEN, Conn. -- Amstar Corp. is negotiating to sell
its Milford Products Corp. saw products unit to the U.S. unit
of Swedish toolmaker Sandvik AB.
   Amstar said the two companies have signed a nonbinding
letter of intent to negotiate a final purchase agreement that
could result in the sale of Milford's stock to Sandvik for
about $20 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Milford, a manufacturer of saw blade products, employs 325
people in plants and distribution centers in Branford, Conn.,
and Banbury, Oxon, England. The transaction is expected to
close in January 1991.
