<HL>
   Who's News:
   Harding Is Named
   A Class A Director
   Of the New York Fed
</HL>
<DATE>
12/28/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE 12
</SO>
<CO>
   WNEWS
</CO>
<IN>
BANKS (BNK)
</IN>
<GV>
FEDERAL RESERVE BOARD (FED)
</GV>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- The Federal Reserve Bank of New York said it
elected Barbara Harding a Class A director for a three-year
term, beginning Jan. 1. Ms. Harding succeeds J. Kirby Fowler,
president and chief executive officer of Flemington National
Bank &amp; Trust Co., Flemington, N.J.
   Ms. Harding is currently chairwoman of Phillipsburg
National Bank &amp; Trust Co., Phillipsburg, N.J., and is also
president and chief executive of its parent holding company,
Vista Bancorp Inc.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Cyrus R. Vance and Ellen V. Futter were reappointed Class
C directors and renamed chairman and vice chairwoman of the
New York Fed's board. Mr. Vance, a former U.S. secretary of
state, is presiding partner at Simpson Thacher &amp; Bartlett, a
New York law firm. Mr. Futter is president of Barnard
College. Their reappointments are for 1991.
   The nine members of this bank's board, as at the other 11
Federal Reserve Banks, are grouped into three classes. Class
A and B directors are elected by small and medium-sized
member banks, respectively. Class C directors are appointed
by the board of governors of the Federal Reserve System in
Washington, D.C.
</TEXT>
