<HL>
   Business Brief -- Westpac Banking Corp.:
   Concern Offers $235 Million
   To Buy New Zealand Thrift
</HL>
<DATE>
12/28/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   WBK
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
SAVINGS AND LOANS, THRIFTS, CREDIT UNIONS (SAL)
</IN>
<LP>
   Westpac Banking Corp. of Wellington, Australia, said it
offered to acquire Southland Building &amp; Investment Society,
New Zealand's biggest mutually owned savings institution with
assets of about 400 million New Zealand dollars (US$235
million).
   A Westpac spokesman wouldn't disclose financial details of
the offer. The 50,000 members of Southland are to hold an
extraordinary meeting in February to consider the offer.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The proposed acquisition is the first expansion by Westpac
in New Zealand in about seven years. If successful, Westpac
intends to maintain Southland as a wholly owned but separate
entity. An application to the Reserve Bank of New Zealand for
a full banking license for Southland would be made if the bid
is successful, Westpac said.
